SQL Practice Questions with Answers

 Q1. How to find the 2nd highest salary from a table?
‚úÖ Answer:

SELECT MAX(salary) FROM employees  
WHERE salary < (SELECT MAX(salary) FROM employees);
üîç Q2. How to find duplicate values in a column?
‚úÖ Answer:

SELECT name, COUNT(*) FROM employees  
GROUP BY name  
HAVING COUNT(*) > 1;
üîç Q3. How to select records that exist in one table but not in another?
‚úÖ Answer:

SELECT * FROM employees  
WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT employee_id FROM payroll);
üîç Q4. How to get the top 3 highest salaries? (MySQL)
‚úÖ Answer:

SELECT DISTINCT salary FROM employees  
ORDER BY salary DESC  
LIMIT 3;
üîç Q5. How to fetch employees with the same salary?
‚úÖ Answer:

SELECT * FROM employees e1  
WHERE EXISTS (  
  SELECT 1 FROM employees e2  
  WHERE e1.salary = e2.salary AND e1.id <> e2.id  
);
üîç Q6. How to get the department-wise highest salary?
‚úÖ Answer:

SELECT department, MAX(salary) AS max_salary  
FROM employees  
GROUP BY department;


